# What `gcloud run deploy --source .` uploads to Cloud Build.
#
# ⚠️ THIS FILE IS LOAD-BEARING. Without it, gcloud falls back to .gitignore —
# which excludes data/outputs/ and data/raw/*.parquet. The build would succeed,
# the container would start, and every endpoint would 404 because the precomputed
# artifacts the agents read were never uploaded. A silent, confusing failure.
#
# So: mirror .dockerignore, and say nothing about data/ (i.e. DO ship it).

# Frontend — deployed separately to Vercel
app/frontend/

# Eval-only ground truth (46 MB). Serving never reads it.
# (path is per-city since the layout split, so glob every city)
data/raw/*/truth.parquet
data/outputs/*/audio/

# Local convenience, not runtime data
data/outputs_snapshots/

# Repo furniture
.git/
.github/
.venv/
venv/
__pycache__/
**/__pycache__/
*.pyc
.pytest_cache/
node_modules/
docs/
.vscode/
.mcp.json

# Secrets must never reach a build context
.env
secrets/
*-service-account.json
*.pem
*.tfstate*
.terraform/
